  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Urdu compound word \u201cghairat-e-ashiq\u201d?",
  "response": "\"Ghairat-e-ashiq\" is an Urdu compound word that can be broken down into two parts:\n\n1. \"Ghairat\" (\u063a\u06cc\u0631\u062a) means honor, dignity, self-respect, or pride.\n2. \"Ashiq\" (\u0639\u0627\u0634\u0642) means lover or one who is in love.\n\nWhen combined, \"ghairat-e-ashiq\" refers to the honor, dignity, or self-respect of a lover. It suggests the sense of pride, devotion, and integrity that a passionate lover maintains in the context of love. The term implies a deep emotional commitment and a sense of honor associated with loving someone.\n\nIn Urdu poetry and romantic literature, this phrase often represents the noble and dignified nature of true love, emphasizing the lover's dedication and emotional depth.",
